00280 /******************************************************************************
00281  NAME
00282     Hfind - locate the next object of a search in an HDF file
00283 
00284  DESCRIPTION
00285     Searches for the `next' DD that fits the search tag/ref.  Wildcards
00286     apply.  If origin is DF_FORWARD, search from current position forwards
00287     in the file, otherwise DF_BACKWARD searches backward from the current
00288     position in the file.  If *find_tag and *find_ref are both set to
00289     0, this indicates the beginning of a search, and the search will
00290     start from the beginning of the file if the direction is DF_FORWARD
00291     and from the and of the file if the direction is DF_BACKWARD.
00292 
00293  RETURNS
00294     returns SUCCEED (0) if successful and FAIL (-1) otherwise
00295 
00296 *******************************************************************************/
00297 HDFLIBAPI intn Hfind(int32 file_id,       /* IN: file ID to search in */
00298         uint16 search_tag,      /* IN: the tag to search for (can be DFTAG_WILDCARD) */
00299         uint16 search_ref,      /* IN: ref to search for (can be DFREF_WILDCARD) */
00300         uint16 *find_tag,       /* IN: if (*find_tag==0) and (*find_ref==0) then start search */
00301                                 /* OUT: tag matching the search tag */
00302         uint16 *find_ref,       /* IN: if (*find_tag==0) and (*find_ref==0) then start search */
00303                                 /* OUT: ref matching the search ref */
00304         int32 *find_offset,     /* OUT: offset of the data element found */
00305         int32 *find_length,     /* OUT: length of the data element found */
00306         intn direction          /* IN: Direction to search in: */
00307                                 /*  DF_FORWARD searches forward from the current location */
00308                                 /*  DF_BACKWARD searches backward from the current location */
00309 );

00331 /************************************************************************
00332 NAME
00333    HDreuse_tagref -- reuse a data descriptor preserving tag/ref
00334 
00335 DESCRIPTION
00336    Reuses the data descriptor of tag/ref in the dd list of the file.
00337    The tag/ref must already exist in the DD list.
00338    This routine is unsafe and may leave a file in a condition that is
00339    not usable by some routines.  Use with care. Not valid for
00340    special elments right now. Used for allowing the data to change
00341    and move somewhere else in the file for non-special elements.
00342    Must be carefully if apply to higher-level objects like GR's and SDS
00343    that are comprised of other objects. 
00344    Usefull when re-writing simple elements whose size changes while
00345    preserving the original tag/ref of the element since other elements
00346    might refer to this element by tag/ref e.g. in a Vgroup.
00347 
00348 RETURNS
00349    returns SUCCEED (0) if successful, FAIL (-1) otherwise
00350 ************************************************************************/
00351 HDFLIBAPI intn 
00352 HDreuse_tagref(int32 file_id, /* IN: id of file */
00353                uint16 tag,    /* IN: tag of data descriptor to reuse */
00354                uint16 ref     /* IN: ref of data descriptor to reuse */ );

01431 /******************************************************************************
01432  NAME
01433       GRsetchunk   -- make GR a chunked GR
01434 
01435  DESCRIPTION
01436       This routine makes the GR a chunked GR according to the chunk
01437       definition passed in.
01438 
01439       The image currently cannot be special already.  i.e. NBIT,
01440       COMPRESSED, or EXTERNAL. This is an Error.
01441 
01442       The defintion of the HDF_CHUNK_DEF union with relvant fields is:
01443 
01444       typedef union hdf_chunk_def_u
01445       {
01446          int32   chunk_lengths[2];  Chunk lengths along each dimension
01447 
01448          struct 
01449           {   
01450             int32     chunk_lengths[2]; Chunk lengths along each dimension
01451             int32     comp_type;                   Compression type 
01452             comp_info cinfo;                       Compression info struct 
01453           }comp;
01454 
01455       } HDF_CHUNK_DEF
01456 
01457       The simplist is the 'chunk_lengths' array specifiying chunk 
01458       lengths for each dimension where the 'flags' argument set to 
01459       'HDF_CHUNK';
01460 
01461       COMPRESSION is set by using the 'HDF_CHUNK_DEF' structure to set the
01462       appropriate compression information along with the required chunk lengths
01463       for each dimension. The compression information is the same as 
01464       that set in 'SDsetcompress()'. The bit-or'd'flags' argument' is set to 
01465       'HDF_CHUNK | HDF_COMP'.
01466 
01467       See the example in pseudo-C below for further usage.
01468 
01469       The maximum number of Chunks in an HDF file is 65,535.
01470 
01471       The performance of the GRxxx interface with chunking is greatly
01472       affected by the users access pattern over the image and by
01473       the maximum number of chunks set in the chunk cache. The cache contains 
01474       the Least Recently Used(LRU cache replacment policy) chunks. See the
01475       routine GRsetchunkcache() for further info on the chunk cache and how 
01476       to set the maximum number of chunks in the chunk cache. A default chunk 
01477       cache is always created.
01478 
01479       The following example shows the organization of chunks for a 2D iamge.
01480       e.g. 4x4 image with 2x2 chunks. The array shows the layout of
01481            chunks in the chunk array.
01482 
01483             4 ---------------------                                           
01484               |         |         |                                                 
01485         Y     |  (0,1)  |  (1,1)  |                                       
01486         ^     |         |         |                                      
01487         |   2 ---------------------                                       
01488         |     |         |         |                                               
01489         |     |  (0,0)  |  (1,0)  |                                      
01490         |     |         |         |                                           
01491         |     ---------------------                                         
01492         |     0         2         4                                       
01493         ---------------> X                                                       
01494                                                                                 
01495         --Without compression--:
01496         {                                                                    
01497         HDF_CHUNK_DEF chunk_def;
01498                                                                             
01499         .......                                                                    
01500         -- Set chunk lengths --                                                    
01501         chunk_def.chunk_lengths[0]= 2;                                                     
01502         chunk_def.chunk_lengths[1]= 2; 
01503 
01504         -- Set Chunking -- 
01505         GRsetchunk(riid, chunk_def, HDF_CHUNK);                      
01506          ......                                                                  
01507         }                                                                           
01508 
01509         --With compression--:
01510         {                                                                    
01511         HDF_CHUNK_DEF chunk_def;
01512                                                                             
01513         .......                
01514         -- Set chunk lengths first --                                                    
01515         chunk_def.chunk_lengths[0]= 2;                                                     
01516         chunk_def.chunk_lengths[1]= 2;
01517 
01518         -- Set compression --
01519         chunk_def.comp.cinfo.deflate.level = 9;
01520         chunk_def.comp.comp_type = COMP_CODE_DEFLATE;
01521 
01522         -- Set Chunking with Compression --
01523         GRsetchunk(riid, chunk_def, HDF_CHUNK | HDF_COMP);                      
01524          ......                                                                  
01525         }                                                                           
01526 
01527  RETURNS
01528         SUCCEED/FAIL
01529 ******************************************************************************/
01530 HDFLIBAPI intn GRsetchunk
01531     (int32 riid,             /* IN: raster access id */
01532      HDF_CHUNK_DEF chunk_def, /* IN: chunk definition */
01533      int32 flags              /* IN: flags */);
01534 
01535 /******************************************************************************
01536  NAME
01537      GRgetchunkinfo -- get Info on GR
01538 
01539  DESCRIPTION
01540      This routine gets any special information on the GR. If its chunked,
01541      chunked and compressed or just a regular GR. Currently it will only
01542      fill the array of chunk lengths for each dimension as specified in
01543      the 'HDF_CHUNK_DEF' union. You can pass in a NULL for 'chunk_def'
01544      if don't want the chunk lengths for each dimension.
01545      Additionaly if successfull it will return a bit-or'd value in 'flags' 
01546      indicating if the GR is:
01547 
01548      Chunked                  -> flags = HDF_CHUNK
01549      Chunked and compressed   -> flags = HDF_CHUNK | HDF_COMP 
01550      Non-chunked              -> flags = HDF_NONE
01551   
01552      e.g. 4x4 array - Pseudo-C
01553      {
01554      int32   rcdims[3];

01556      int32   cflags;
01557      ...
01558      rchunk_def.chunk_lengths = rcdims;
01559      GRgetchunkinfo(riid, &rchunk_def, &cflags);
01560      ...
01561      }

01623 /******************************************************************************
01624 NAME
01625      GRsetchunkcache -- maximum number of chunks to cache 
01626 
01627 DESCRIPTION
01628      Set the maximum number of chunks to cache.
01629 
01630      The cache contains the Least Recently Used(LRU cache replacment policy) 
01631      chunks. This routine allows the setting of maximum number of chunks that 
01632      can be cached, 'maxcache'.
01633 
01634      The performance of the GRxxx interface with chunking is greatly
01635      affected by the users access pattern over the image and by
01636      the maximum number of chunks set in the chunk cache. The number chunks 
01637      that can be set in the cache is process memory limited. It is a good 
01638      idea to always set the maximum number of chunks in the cache as the 
01639      default heuristic does not take into account the memory available for 
01640      the application.
01641 
01642      By default when the GR is promoted to a chunked element the 
01643      maximum number of chunks in the cache 'maxcache' is set to the number of
01644      chunks along the last dimension.
01645 
01646      The values set here affects the current object's caching behaviour.
01647 
01648      If the chunk cache is full and 'maxcache' is greater then the
01649      current 'maxcache' value, then the chunk cache is reset to the new
01650      'maxcache' value, else the chunk cache remains at the current
01651      'maxcache' value.
01652 
01653      If the chunk cache is not full, then the chunk cache is set to the
01654      new 'maxcache' value only if the new 'maxcache' value is greater than the
01655      current number of chunks in the cache.
01656 
01657      Use flags argument of 'HDF_CACHEALL' if the whole object is to be cached 
01658      in memory, otherwise pass in zero(0). Currently you can only
01659      pass in zero.
01660 
01661     See GRsetchunk() for a description of the organization of chunks in an GR.
01662 
01663 RETURNS
01664      Returns the 'maxcache' value for the chunk cache if successful 
01665      and FAIL otherwise
01666 ******************************************************************************/
01667 HDFLIBAPI intn GRsetchunkcache
01668     (int32 riid,     /* IN: raster access id */
01669      int32 maxcache,  /* IN: max number of chunks to cache */
01670      int32 flags      /* IN: flags = 0, HDF_CACHEALL */);
